 {"id":"bd-d9o","title":"[I/O] Implement AsyncWrite Trait and Extensions","description":"# AsyncWrite Trait Implementation

## Overview
Define and implement the AsyncWrite trait for non-blocking write operations with two-phase commit for cancel-safety.

## Core Trait

```rust
use std::io;
use std::pin::Pin;
use std::task::{Context, Poll};

/// Async non-blocking write
pub trait AsyncWrite {
    /// Attempt to write buf
    fn poll_write(
        self: Pin<&mut Self>,
        cx: &mut Context<'_>,
        buf: &[u8],
    ) -> Poll<io::Result<usize>>;

    /// Attempt to write all bufs (vectored)
    fn poll_write_vectored(
        self: Pin<&mut Self>,
        cx: &mut Context<'_>,
        bufs: &[io::IoSlice<'_>],
    ) -> Poll<io::Result<usize>> {
        // Default: write first non-empty buffer
        default_poll_write_vectored(self, cx, bufs)
    }

    /// Check if vectored writes are efficient
    fn is_write_vectored(&self) -> bool {
        false
    }

    /// Flush buffered data
    fn poll_flush(
        self: Pin<&mut Self>,
        cx: &mut Context<'_>,
    ) -> Poll<io::Result<()>>;

    /// Shutdown the writer
    fn poll_shutdown(
        self: Pin<&mut Self>,
        cx: &mut Context<'_>,
    ) -> Poll<io::Result<()>>;
}
```

## Extension Trait

```rust
pub trait AsyncWriteExt: AsyncWrite {
    /// Write all bytes
    fn write_all<'a>(&'a mut self, buf: &'a [u8]) -> WriteAll<'a, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Write all bytes from buffer
    fn write_all_buf<'a, B: Buf>(&'a mut self, buf: &'a mut B) -> WriteAllBuf<'a, Self, B>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Write single byte
    fn write_u8(&mut self, n: u8) -> WriteU8<'_, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Flush
    fn flush(&mut self) -> Flush<'_, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;

    /// Shutdown
    fn shutdown(&mut self) -> Shutdown<'_, Self>
    where
        Self: Unpin;
}
```

## Two-Phase Write (Cancel-Safe)

For truly cancel-safe writes, use WritePermit pattern:

```rust
/// Reserve write capacity
pub struct WritePermit<'a, W: AsyncWrite + ?Sized> {
    writer: &'a mut W,
    data: Vec<u8>,
}

impl<'a, W: AsyncWrite + Unpin + ?Sized> WritePermit<'a, W> {
    /// Reserve space for writing
    pub async fn reserve(writer: &'a mut W, len: usize) -> io::Result<Self> {
        Ok(WritePermit {
            writer,
            data: Vec::with_capacity(len),
        })
    }

    /// Stage data for writing
    pub fn stage(&mut self, data: &[u8]) {
        self.data.extend_from_slice(data);
    }

    /// Commit the write (consumes permit)
    pub async fn commit(mut self) -> io::Result<()> {
        self.writer.write_all(&self.data).await
    }
}

impl<W: AsyncWrite + ?Sized> Drop for WritePermit<'_, W> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        // Data discarded if not committed - explicit abort
    }
}
```

## Future Types

```rust
/// Future for write_all
pub struct WriteAll<'a, W: ?Sized> {
    writer: &'a mut W,
    buf: &'a [u8],
    pos: usize,
}

impl<W: AsyncWrite + Unpin + ?Sized> Future for WriteAll<'_, W> {
    type Output = io::Result<()>;

    fn poll(self: Pin<&mut Self>, cx: &mut Context<'_>) -> Poll<Self::Output> {
        let this = self.get_mut();
        while this.pos < this.buf.len() {
            let n = ready!(Pin::new(&mut *this.writer)
                .poll_write(cx, &this.buf[this.pos..]))?;

            if n == 0 {
                return Poll::Ready(Err(io::Error::from(io::ErrorKind::WriteZero)));
            }
            this.pos += n;
        }
        Poll::Ready(Ok(()))
    }
}
```

## Cancel-Safety Analysis
- poll_write: cancel-safe (partial write OK)
- write_all: NOT cancel-safe (partial state)
- WritePermit: cancel-safe (uncommitted data dropped)
- flush: cancel-safe (can retry)
- shutdown: cancel-safe (idempotent)

## Implementations
- impl AsyncWrite for Vec<u8>
- impl AsyncWrite for Cursor<&mut [u8]>
- impl<W: AsyncWrite + ?Sized> AsyncWrite for &mut W
- impl<W: AsyncWrite + ?Sized> AsyncWrite for Box<W>

